# Code-owners for review routing. See
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/managing-repository-settings/about-code-owners
#
# `@CepheusLabs/<team>` references kick in once each named team is
# created on github.com/CepheusLabs (team names below are intentionally
# stable so adding/removing humans is a zero-diff change here). When
# a team doesn't yet exist GitHub silently ignores the entry and the
# global default at the top wins, so this file is safe to land
# before the teams do.

# Default owner.
* @CepheusLabs

# Privileged surfaces — anything that can corrupt a disk, escape
# the sandbox, or fetch profile-supplied code. Two-team review.
/sidecar/internal/disks/                @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
/sidecar/cmd/deckhand-elevated-helper/  @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
/packages/deckhand_flash/               @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
/packages/deckhand_profile_script/      @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
/packages/deckhand_profile_lint/        @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
/SECURITY.md                            @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security

# Release pipeline — packaging, signing, SBOM, manifest.
/packaging/                             @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/release
/.github/workflows/release.yml          @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/release
/.github/workflows/security.yml         @CepheusLabs @CepheusLabs/security
